<recommendation type="For Fans" uid="396857">Hmm...I personally didn`t really feel it to be honest...None of the three movies were bad or anything, but I personally only really liked the second one...*shrug*

Mary &amp; The Witch`s Flower was better. But then that is to be expected, since that was a feature film. Still, that movie also doesn`t really quite reach up to Ghibli`s level. It started out great, but then waned a bit as the movie carried on, I feel. Studio Ponoc still has a way to go before I would consider them a good replacement for Ghibli, but of course I`m grateful to them for carrying on the torch. I guess I`m just a bit disappointed since I loved Yonebayashi`s work on Arrietty and Marnie, so I was expecting more from him...</recommendation>
